The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, April 01, 2004  BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 										Khan stable, conscious				 										Calcutta: Amjad Khans condition was learnt to be stable on Wednesday. The jockey had suffered severe head injuries after he fell off his mount Bit of Luck at the RCTC races last Friday. 				 										He has been taken is off the artificial respirator for more than 24 hours. He is being fed through tubes which are likely to be removed tomorrow. said a medical officer at the Woodlands hospital where the jockey				 										was rushed after the accident. The jockey has regained consciousness, though he is still feeling irritable, added the hospital source. However, it may take another four weeks before he is discharged from the hospital.
